---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Us | Heartland Chasers"
	description="Meet Ike and Jess, the storm chasers behind Heartland Chasers, documenting severe weather across the Midwest."
>
	<Nav slot="nav" />

	<main>
		<section>
			<h1>About Heartland Chasers</h1>
			<p>
				Heartland Chasers is a Midwest storm chasing team built around curiosity, respect for the
				weather, and a commitment to sharing what we see from the road.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Who We Are</h2>
			<p>
				Ike and Jess travel across Wisconsin, Minnesota, Iowa, Illinois, Indiana, and the Dakotas
				following severe weather. What started as a passion for watching the sky has grown into a
				mission to document storms, learn forecasting and safety, and tell the stories behind the
				chase.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>What We Do</h2>
			<p>
				We chase with cameras rolling, radar open, and safety first. Our work includes live streams
				during active chases, photo and video galleries, chase reports with radar notes, and lessons
				learned from each trip. We aim to educate, inspire, and connect with the storm chasing
				community and anyone fascinated by severe weather.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Our Approach</h2>
			<p>
				Storm chasing demands preparation, patience, and humility. We study forecasts, respect road
				and storm safety, and prioritize accurate reporting over hype. Every chase is a chance to
				learn — and to share that learning with others.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Follow Along</h2>
			<p>
				Watch our live streams when we are on the road, browse the gallery for photos from past
				chases, or reach out if you would like to connect.
			</p>
			<a class="button" href="/gallery">View Gallery</a>
			<a class="button" href="/contact">Contact Us</a>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
